# Project Deployment Restructuring Plan

## Goal
Structure the project for a standard production-ready Flask deployment (compatible with platforms like Render, Heroku, etc.), and add comprehensive documentation.

## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> This change involves moving files ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/index.html), [js/](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/js/components/ml-demos.js), `assets/`) into standard Flask folders (`templates/`, [static/](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/server.py#69-73)). This will break file paths if the HTML is opened directly (without the server). The user *must* run the server to view the site after this change.

## Proposed Changes

### File Organization
-   **Create folder `templates/`**: Move [index.html](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/index.html) here.
-   **Create folder [static/](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/server.py#69-73)**:
    -   Move [js/](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/js/components/ml-demos.js) folder here.
    -   Move `assets/` folder here.
    -   Move `resume_file/` folder here (so the resume PDF can be served).
    -   (Note: `style.css` is referenced as [static/style.css](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/static/style.css) in [index.html](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/index.html), so verify if [static](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/server.py#69-73) already exists and what's in it).

### Code Changes
#### [MODIFY] [server.py](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/server.py)
-   Change `app` initialization to use default struct (`static_folder='static'`, `template_folder='templates'`).
-   Update routes:
    -   `@app.route('/')` should `return render_template('index.html')`.
    -   Remove the "catch-all" static server route that was insecure.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/index.html) (now in `templates/`)
-   Update resource links to use [static/](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/server.py#69-73) prefix relative to the root URL (or Jinja2 `url_for` if we want to go full Flask, but keeping it simple with `/static/...` paths allows easier understanding).
-   Paths to update:
    -   `js/...` -> `/static/js/...` (or `static/js/...`)
    -   `assets/...` -> `/static/assets/...`
    -   `resume_file/...` -> `/static/resume_file/...`
    -   `static/style.css` -> `/static/style.css` (check if this was already inside `static`).

### New Files
#### [NEW] [Procfile](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/Procfile)
-   `web: gunicorn server:app`

#### [NEW] [README.md](file:///c:/Users/deepb/OneDrive/Desktop/resume_project/README.md)
-   Project setup, installation, running instructions, and deployment guide.

## Verification Plan
1.  **Move Files**: Execute the moves.
2.  **Start Server**: Run `python server.py`.
3.  **Check Site**: Open `http://localhost:5000`.
    -   Verify images load.
    -   Verify JS loads (console should be clean).
    -   Verify CSS loads.
4.  **Check Resume Download**: Ensure the resume link works.
